This paper belongs to the field of computer security (cs.CR) as it deals with online scams and the use of typosquatting domains to trick users. It also involves the use of JavaScript and HTTP user agents, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cyber security (cs.CY), social and information networks (cs.SI), software engineering (cs.SE), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
